title: The State Fair Affair: a massacre on machinery hil
St. Peter Time Trial
description:
St. Peter Time Trial 40K/20K for Juniors/Masters 60+
ROY Event
Sponsored by St. Paul Bicycling Racing Club
course: 40K out and back course beginning approximately 100 meter W of the intersection of W Trverse Rd and Edgerton St.  Riders will ride W 2.7 km on W Traverse Rd, turn left and ride 17.3 km on Cty Hwy 15/Cty Rd 15, turn around and then ride back to the start.  The course for the Juniors and Masters will be 20K.
registration: Pre-registration at SportsBaseOnline.com before Thursday June4, 2009.  Fee $25 for USCF-licensed riders; $15 for juniors.  On-site registration $30 for USCF-licensed riders; $15 juniors. One-day licenses are available for an additional fee.  Registration opens 7:30AM day of race 6/6/09 and closes at 8:45AM. Registration located at First Lutheran Church in St. Peter, MN @ intersection of W Traverse Road and Edgerton Street (~200 meters from the race start).  All USCF rules apply. Helmets mandatory and shirts must cover shoulders.  No fringes allowed. The course is NOT closed to traffic.  The yellow line rule will be enforced. The first rider will depart at 9:00AM. Subsequent riders will depart at 30 second intervals.  All riders must checkin, sign the release and pick up race number vefore 8:45AM.  Start order: first to register, first to ride order of line-up at every 30 second intervals. Riders should be at the start line a minimum of 3 minutes prior to their start time.  Prizes noed by $$ will be $35 for fisrt place, $15 for second, and swag (merchandise) for third.  Prizes noted by swag will be swag for first, second, and third place.
directions: From Minneapolis/St. Paul, MN. take Hwy 169 South to St. Peter, MN. (approx. 1-1.5 hr. drive)
